page.content: {COMMON FLOWERS {NAME HABITAT DESCRIPTION Daisy Meadow Pink/White Buttercup Meadow Yellow Dandelion Meadow Yellow Dead Nettle Wayside White Yellow Iris Marshland Yellow {NATIVE TREES Oak Grassland Lobed Leaves Ash Grassland Grey Bark Hawthorn Widespread Sharp Thorned Chestnut Widespread Palmate Leaves Birch Widespread Silver Bark {FAUNA OF AREA Most common animals:_ hedgehog,rabbit fieldmouse, vole and mole. Many foxes found; frequent visitors to gardens. Water voles by ponds and streams. Reptiles include:_ adder, grass snake, frog, toad and newt. Usual garden and woodland birds, herons and birds of prey e.g. kestrels.
